n## QTRAIN to develop the first commercially available quantum transceiver\n![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6721f6603ca1e674e1539dfb/690b5d1fa66e9b1a75939aed_QTRAIN.jpeg)\n![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6721f6603ca1e674e1539db4/67220ffe36d9614e9fc0dc64_Vectors-Wrapper.svg)\nNews\nNovember 24, 2025\n# QTRAIN to develop the first commercially available quantum transceiver\nSparrow Quantum, [Single Quantum](https://www.singlequantum.com/), [Refined Laser Systems](https://refined-lasers.com/), and the [Ruhr-Universit\u00e4t Bochum](https://www.ruhr-uni-bochum.de/en) have joined forces to launch an exciting new initiative: the Quantum Transceiver Based on Deterministic Single-Photon Sources (QTRAIN).\nBacked by global R&D funding network [EUREKA](https://www.eurekanetwork.org/), QTRAIN aims to develop a single-photon quantum transceiver by January 2027. The QTRAIN transceiver would represent the first quantum transceiver on the market and the most advanced photon detection unit commercially available, with notable improvements in energy consumption, space efficiency, and overall cost. \n**DEFINING THE GOALS**\nLike any quantum transceiver, the QTRAIN transceiver will be able to both transmit and receive data, making it a potent tool for secure quantum communications. However, QTRAIN will improve on previous iterations of this technology by housing the single-photon source and the single-photon detectors within the same cryostat at the O-band telecom wavelength.\nThe QTRAIN model has great implications for quantum computing and communications. Using best-in-class technologies from each consortium partner, the QTRAIN system is expected to reduce the transceiver\u2019s physical footprint by50%; lower energy consumption by 60%; improve general ease of operation; and reduce purchase, installation, and maintenance costs. \n**REALISING THE VISION**\nThe four consortium partners will contribute their specialised expertise to different stages of the project: \n\u00b7 The Ruhr-Universit\u00e4t Bochum has pioneered the use of a new and exclusive material for QTRAIN, producing high-quality quantum dots at 1310 mm.\n\u00b7 Refined Laser Systems will provide the lasers needed to excite the quantum dots. The lasers will emit pulses at the rate of 120 megahertz. \n\u00b7 Sparrow Quantum supplies deterministic single-photon sources, notably its flagship [Sparrow Core](https://sparrowquantum.com/product). Upon receiving a laser pulse at the correct rate and wavelength, the source will emit a single photon in free space, which will then proceed to the photon detector.\n\u00b7 Single Quantum will manufacture the photon detectors and the cryostat in which both source and detector are contained. Assembly will take place at Single Quantum\u2019s headquarters in Delft, NL. \n**BRINGING TO MARKET**\nAnalysts have remarked that many universities and businesses have failed to fully benefit from the recent wave of quantum advancements. One cause of this deficiency is the presence of consistently high barriers to adoption, not least the cost of initial installation. \nA key aspect of QTRAIN is that the new transceiver not only represents a technological improvement but also lowers barriers to adoption by making this technology cheaper and easier to operate. That\u2019s why the QTRAIN transceiver will be the first quantum receiver available for commercial purchase, representing the first attempt to scale this technology to a level appropriate for the commercial sphere. \nOutside of the consortium, other institutions have signaled confidence in QTRAIN\u2019s commercial potential. Companies have already indicated interest in testing the QTRAIN transceiver and integrating the technology into their own offerings. \nNews\nNovember 24, 2025\nInvestment from the Innovation Fund Denmark: 16.2 million kroner. \nDuration: 5 years. \nOfficial title: FTQP \u2013 \u2018Fault-Tolerant Architectures for Quantum Computing with Photon Emitters\u2019. \n![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6721f6603ca1e674e1539db4/67220ffe36d9614e9fc0dc64_Vectors-Wrapper.svg)\n### News\nStay updated with our latest news and insights. Check back regularly for updates on Sparrow Quantum and our industry.\n[![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6721f6603ca1e674e1539dfb/68f9d4de9a632d41af467e47_AdobeStock_601607813.jpg) News October 23, 2025 Stitching light across time could simplify quantum computers ](https://sparrowquantum.com/post/stitching-light-across-time-could-simplify-quantum-computers)\n[![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6721f6603ca1e674e1539dfb/67472d0b15de91cf03408e63_Product-bg-img-03.jpg) News May 11, 2023 Rekordstor startkapital til det danske kvanteteknologifirma, Sparrow Quantum ](https://sparrowquantum.com/post/rekordstor-startkapital-til-det-danske-kvanteteknologifirma-sparrow-quantum)\n[![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6721f6603ca1e674e1539dfb/67472dcb4f9923d7676008ba_Group-42%201.jpg) News November 22, 2022 Danske kvanteforskere st\u00e5r bag verdensnyhed, der kan afv\u00e6rge cyberangreb ](https://sparrowquantum.com/post/danske-kvanteforskere-staar-bag-verdensnyhed-der-kan-afvaerg-cyberangreb)\n[![Sparrow Quantum logo with blue gradient color](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6721f6603ca1e674e1539db4/6728a5364585a64f06e02a6e_Logo%20-%20Left%20Aligned.svg)](https://sparrowquantum.com/post/qtrain-to-develop-the-first-commercially-available-quantum-transceiver)\nUnlocking Quantum Breakthroughs,   \nOne Photon at a Time\nAddress\n[Nordre Fasanvej 215  \n2000 Frederiksberg  \nDenmark  \nCVR. 36998717](https://maps.app.goo.gl/LhwCTfMwYQrr9w1R8)\nInfo\ninfo@sparrowquantum.com[+ 45 31 13 66 55](tel:+4531136655)[Privacy Policy](https://sparrowquantum.com/privacy-policy)\nSocials\n[LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/sparrow-quantum/)[X](https://x.com/sparrow_quantum)[Youtube](https://www.youtube.com/@SparrowQuantum)\n\u00a92026 - Sparrow Quantum\n",
